## Example 2

```
y = 64
```

```
z = 64

x = 64 / 2 + 1

= 32 + 1

= 33
```

---

## Example 3

```
y = 25
```

```
z = 25

x = 25 / 2 + 1

= 12 + 1

= 13
```

Notice something important.

```
25 / 2

=

12

not

12.5
```

because Solidity discards the decimal part during integer division.

